Package: ferx
Title: Nonlinear Mixed Effects Modeling with Rust Backend
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("InsightRx", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "dev@insightrx.com")
Description: Fast NLME estimation using FOCE/FOCEI with automatic differentiation.
    Powered by a Rust engine with Enzyme autodiff for exact gradients.
    Supports analytical PK models (1/2-compartment) and ODE-based models.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
SystemRequirements: Rust (>= 1.70), Cargo; optionally Enzyme toolchain for autodiff
Config/rextendr/version: 0.3.1
